    b"mory search before the selected task runs.\x0a\x0a        Stop once the hints look goo"
    b"d enough for the request without thinking about it too much.\x0a\x0a        Search sur"
    b"faces:\x0a        - tags: exact memory tags. They are not substring searched.\x0a     "
    b"   - strings.contains: case-insensitive text fragments. Each value is checked\x0a  "
    b"        as a substring against searchable memory content.\x0a        - strings.equa"
    b"ls: exact text values. Each value is checked for exact\x0a          equality agains"
    b"t searchable memory content.\x0a\x0a        Optional outputs available in this step:\x0a "
    b"       - candidate_memory: a vague remembered observation that could be useful t"
    b"o\x0a          preserve.\x0a\x0a        Rules:\x0a        - Return only search hints and opt"
    b"ional candidate_memory.\x0a        - Search hints are alternatives during retrieval"
    b"; a memory can be useful\x0a          when any positive tag or string hint matches."
    b"\x0a        - Prefer tags.any_of for positive tag hints.\x0a        - Leave tags.all_o"
    b"f empty unless compatibility with older memories needs it.\x0a        - Use tags.no"
    b"ne_of only for clear exclusions.\x0a        - Use strings.contains for durable word"
    b"s or phrases that should appear\x0a          inside a relevant memory.\x0a        - Us"
    b"e strings.equals only for exact text that should match a relevant\x0a          memo"
    b"ry value as a whole.\x0a        - Prefer a small set of high-signal hints over broa"
    b"d keyword stuffing.\x0a        - Return empty arrays when no useful search hint is "
